doc.previous: On November 24, 2014, a Cargolux 747-8F performed a hard landing at Libreville, Gabon. Extensive structural damage was found at December 2. The aircraft was repaired at Luxemburg by a Boeing team. After more than 4 months of repairs, it flew on April 7, 2015 during a test.[citation needed]
